  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0dda\u0dad\u0dba \u0daf\u0dd2\u0d9c\u0dda \u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2 50\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d87\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "50 lakhs have come along the code",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Q.R. of the National Fuel License. As of last night (31) 50 lakh vehicles were registered to get fuel from the code and 1,140 gas stations were registered. Electricity and Energy Minister Mr. Kanchana Wijesekera said that they had adapted to release fuel through the system.",
        "Of those 1,140 gas stations, there are 964 Cipetco stations and I.O.C. Ministry of Energy data shows that there are 176 filling stations and 10 million liters of fuel were given yesterday through those filling stations.",
        "The data also shows that the 50 lakh registered vehicles include 2,891,260 motorcycles, 876,158 three-wheelers and 651,314 cars."
      ],
